text:
Maurice Ave. (foreground, steam shovel thereon), from about Fifty-second Ave. (left), to 53rd Drive (right), showing a part of the Ridgewood Plateau. The four story building in View No. 2 is on the N.E. corner of 53rd Drive and 65th Street. These views form a panoramic scene, in the center of which was a gypsy encampment, at an earlier date. September 1929.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
